To modify the HTML we recreate the image and upload it to the repo

1) Modify your HTML file as needed on your local machine.

2) Build a new Docker image with the updated HTML file using your existing Dockerfile. 
sudo docker build -t docker_image:lab .

3) Tag it
sudo docker tag docker_image:lab nanogk/docker_image:lab

4) Upload to private repo
sudo docker push nanogk/docker_image:lab




Dockerfile to create image:
# Use the official Nginx base image
FROM nginx
# Copy your HTML and other files into the container
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/

Build and Push to docker repo:
1) login to docker via cli: docker login
2) Docker Build: sudo docker build -t nanogk/dockerrepo:lab .
3) Docker push: sudo docker push nanogk/dockerrepo:lab



x) tag the image: sudo docker tag docker_image:lab nanogk/dockerrepo:lab
